The paper discusses the use of network proximity rules for location-based services, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). It also involves machine learning techniques for predicting user behavior, which could be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the potential benefits for energy saving on mobile devices, which could be categorized under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and systems and control (cs.SY).
